<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="175" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="175">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="175">Small to moderately-sized insect (forewing length 5.1-15.4 mm); body slender; wing nearly oval or rounded apically. Forewing: Sc with two or three branches ending at C; Rs (R2 to R5) origination distad of M origination; Rs forking with four (in some cases with five) branches; M forking with four (in some cases with five) branches. Hind wing: Sc simple and short, terminating at C well before pterostigma; Rs forking with four branches; M forking with four branches (in some cases with five).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
